## 9. REVENUE MODEL & MONETIZATION

### 9.1 Revenue Streams

| Revenue Stream | Unit Economics | Monthly Estimate (500K MAU) |
|---|---|---|
| **Event Creation Fee** | ₹99-₹499 per event | ₹25-50 lakh (50K events) |
| **Booking Commission** | 10% of event fees | ₹50-100 lakh (avg ₹50K/day events) |
| **Payment Processing** | 2.36% + ₹0 (Razorpay) | ₹10-20 lakh (absorbed for now) |
| **Sponsored Events/Ads** | Premium placement in feed | ₹10-30 lakh (future) |
| **Subscription (Premium Host)** | ₹299-₹999/month (future) | ₹5-10 lakh (future) |
| **Venue Partnerships** | Revenue sharing | ₹5-10 lakh (future) |

**Total Projected Annual Revenue (Year 1)**: ₹3-5 Crore

### 9.2 Pricing Strategy

**Event Creation Fee Tiers**:
- **Standard Sports** (Football, Badminton, Cricket, Tennis, Badminton): ₹99
- **Fitness & Wellness** (Yoga, Running, Gym, Pilates, Meditation): ₹199
- **Niche & Creative Events** (Cacao Ceremony, Book Club, Art Class, Pottery, Wine Tasting): ₹299
- **Large Group/Corporate Events** (Tournaments, Team-Building, Corporate Wellness): ₹499

**Rationale**:
- Creates quality barrier (serious hosts pay upfront)
- Tiered pricing incentivizes niche community building
- Non-refundable, even if event cancelled (platform retains for operational costs)

**Booking Commission**: 
- 10% platform commission on all event entry fees (host gets 90%)
- Transparent breakdown shown to host at time of creation
- Applies only to paid events, not free community events

