## 12. RISK MITIGATION & CONTINGENCIES

### 12.1 Key Risks

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|-----------|
| **Low host adoption** (paying ₹99 creates friction) | Medium | High | Launch with free creation fees for first 10 events; gradual paywall introduction |
| **Quality issues** (fake hosts, cancelled events) | Medium | High | Strict verification, reputation badges, review-based ranking, trust ratings |
| **Payment gateway failures** (Razorpay downtime) | Low | High | Implement Stripe backup; offline payment queuing |
| **User retention** (low repeat booking rate) | Medium | High | Strong onboarding, push notifications, community features (chat, leaderboards) |
| **Competitor acquisition** (Playo + Turf Town bundle events) | Medium | Medium | Focus on niche events + customization (difficult for incumbents); build community moat |
| **Regulatory issues** (FSSAI food safety for cacao ceremonies) | Low | High | Legal review per event type; host indemnification; insurance partnerships |
| **Venue partnerships** (turfs don't integrate APIs) | Medium | Medium | Start with manual venue entry; gradual partnership expansion |
| **Chat toxicity** (harassment, scams in messages) | Low | Medium | AI content moderation; user blocking; incident escalation; community guidelines enforcement |

### 12.2 Contingencies

**If event creation fees reduce adoption**:
- Revert to 100% free creation (revenue from booking commissions only)
- A/B test pricing ($2 vs ₹99 vs ₹199)
- Offer "free first event" coupon for new hosts

**If competitor (Playo/Turf Town) launches event customization**:
- Double down on niche event ecosystem + community features
- Develop advanced AI-powered matchmaking
- Build host revenue programs (help hosts earn more)

**If payment gateway fails**:
- Maintain backup payment gateway (Stripe)
- Implement offline booking with delayed payment settlement
- Clear user communication (grace period, automatic retry)

